Letting B denote the bride’s age, we have that B/2 + 15 = groom’s age. So, we can write the age sum as B/2 + 15 + B. Since this sum is 51, we have
\begin{align*}
B/2 + 15 + B &= 51 \\
\Rightarrow\quad B + 15/2 + B &= 51 \\
\Rightarrow\quad 2B + 15 &= 51 \\
\Rightarrow\quad 2B &= 36 \\
\Rightarrow\quad B &= 18 \\
\Rightarrow\quad \text{groom's age} &= B/2 + 15 = 18/2 + 15 = \boxed{21}
\end{align*}
